From the brand

Previous page

  2. Who are EldonCard?

    We are a Danish manufacturer of dry format cards for blood grouping. Based on an invention by the Danish physician Knud Eldon, EldonCards have been manufactured and used for over 40 years. Millions of cards have been utilized to establish individuals blood group within the AB0-Rhesus (D) systems and to ensure compatibility of patient/donor blood. Today EldonCards are based on special formulations of monoclonal antibodies.

  3. Why Do I Need to Know My Blood Type.

    Knowing your blood type can help you understand your health better. It could save your life if you needed an emergency blood transfusion. EldonCard is the most trusted and accurate diagnostic test kit for blood types of ABO-, and Rhesus. Know your blood type within minutes with EldonCard!

  4. The EldonCard is extremely safe to use.

    It is very accurate and using the card eliminates many of the possible human errors associated with the traditional laboratory-based methodologies, where blood type testing is done with liquid reagents on a glass plate. It also leaves a permanent record the EldonCard which can either be included in a patient journal or it can be given to the patient for safekeeping.

  5. The EldonCard is a product of the highest quality.

    It is ISO certified, CE marked in the EU, cleared in the US, as well as being registered with relevant authorities in a range of other countries. The EldonCard is made of a special type of plastic upon which dried antibody formulations are placed. The EldonCard is a reliable, durable, and flexible point-of-care blood typing system.

  6. The EldonCard is extremely accurate.

    It has been tested against the standard blood typing procedure using directly agglutinating antibodies. Tests have been performed at several laboratories in different countries and the results have matched those achieved by the EldonCard and a test using a standard blood typing procedure.

  7. What's included in each pack

    1 EldonCard, 2 x Sterile Lancets, 1 x Pipet, 1 x Alcohol Wipe, 4 x EldonSticks, Clear Illustrated, Instructions and 1x EldonFoil

From the manufacturer

About Us

ELDON BIOLOGICALS A/S is a Danish manufacturer of dry format cards for blood grouping. Based on an invention by the Danish physician Knud Eldon, EldonCards have been manufactured and used for more than 40 years. Over time millions of cards have been utilised to establish individuals blood group within the AB0-Rhesus (D) systems and to ensure compatibility of patient/donor blood. Today EldonCards are based on the use of special formulations of selected monoclonal antibodies.

Product Description

Easy, Self-testing Blood Type Kit - Everything you need to discover your blood type and rhesus factor in the comfort of your own home - pain free.This affordable kit comes complete with everything you need, including instructions, finger lancet and alcohol prep, plastic applicator sticks and testing card. Performing the test is easy. After first cleaning with the supplied alcohol prep pad, the finger is lanced with the sterile disposable lancet. The hand is then turned downward and a drop of blood is placed on top of each of the four sticks. The sticks are then applied to the card, and stirred for two minutes. The results are then read from the card. Total time to results is less than six minutes. Single use blood typing kit (for educational purposes only).

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

4 Stars
Alcohol Wipe Totally Dried Out! Type O Positive
One star deducted for having the alcohol wipe be totally dry, making have to go get isopropyl alcohol to clean my finger when I was already nervous about the lancet! My test was still good (according to dates on the package) for another year-and-seven-months!***********************************************************************It was waiting in the kitchen for my bloodI kept finding other things to do.Anything to keep busy and stave off having to draw blood from my finger using the lancet in my brand-new blood group test kit that arrived in the mail today. Its an EldonCard blood group test kit.ABO/Rh Blood Typing KitI wanted to know if I was A, B, AB, O and + or just like they talk about on TV. Plus know what velcro tactical morale blood type patch to buy for my jacket.Blood isnt this simple actually!Did you know there are thirty-six different blood type systems? The ABO and Rh Resus factor are just two systems that this card tests. Then there are the differences between Red Blood and just plasma, it seems simple, but its really dumbed-down by doctors (and movies and TV shows).Actually, the EldonCard only tests parts of the ABO and Rh systems: the Rh factor has 49 different types but were only checking for one: positive or negative (circle D). As far as the ABO part: blood type A has around 20 different subgroups, some of which are not interchangeable! There are over 300 different antigens that can be tested for in the different blood type systems.So what does this kit do?Basically, the A circle has anti-A chemicals on it, which clot up it touches A blood. The B circle has b antigens that clot up if it touches B blood. When you look at the clotted blood: it looks like polka dots which is why you need to NOT give certain people certain blood types during a transfusion: all their blood with clot up and kill them.Huh? What does this kit show?There are four circles: A, B, D and Control:If A clots: youre type A.If B clots: youre type B.If A & B both clot: youre type AB.If neither A or B clot: youre type O.If Circle D clots youre positive.If Circle D does NOT clot youre negative.Circle Control: if this clots you messed up the test/it was defective from the factory. Buy a new Eldoncard!How do you use the kit?1. You put a drop of water on each of the circles.2. Wipe your finger with the alcohol wipe (mine came dried out, so I used 70% isopropyl alcohol). Wave your hand around to pool blood into your fingers.3. Jab your finger with the spring-loaded lancet. I actually had a family member force my finger onto the spring-loaded lancet because I was too scared. It finally went off and laughed at the non-pain, thats all?, LOL!4. Touch one of the four provided dabbers to your bloody finger and swirl it onto the water drop in one of the circles. Throw away the dabber and grab a new dabber (one dabber per circle, no mixing allowed).Right before your eyes youll either have a pretty even smear of blood, or the smear will very quickly start clumping (agglutination) right before your eyes.Im sorry, but the results are positive.As you can see in my test photo, only Circle D (#3) clumped up.This means: no A, no B so Im an O with a Positive Rh: so that makes me Type O Positive. I was actually hoping for type o negative because thats the universal donor (and also the name of a really cool goth metal band).This allowed me to order the appropriate velcro tactical morale patches from Amazon. Lets say I have one of these patches on a jacket, and a Charmin delivery truck driver shoots at some toilet paper hijackers and a stray bullet hits my arm: the hospital will pay NO attention to it and do their own tests, even when I say dont prick my finger, I already did an $8 test in my kitchen while sucking down a Red Bull during the great coronavirus shutdown of 2020! and I'm pretty sure I read the results correctly...wait, this *isn't* my jacket!Why on Earth would you do such a thing?I hear this phrase a lot in my life, LOL!Nowhere in my medical records was my blood type listed.My doctors couldnt tell me.I cant donate blood (which is how most Americans learn their blood type).My doctor wouldnt order a blood type test because there was no immediate needand theres no real use because if you need a transfusion they will retest anyway since the consequences are so dire (imagine all your blood clumping like it does on the test card).Plus it was only $8 off Amazon, although two days later the price has been jacked up to $15 with Prime! This would be a cool project for a kid in school (take the test, document results, write a report).I did have a DNA test with 23&Me years ago and they said I was "probably" a type o, but they couldn't be sure. That blood type info has disappeared off their medical results page. I decided to see if it was true.Anywayit seemed like a good idea at the time.*****UPDATE 2021: I had another surgery and this time they actually tested my blood (weird that they didn't for the previous surgery) and on my online medical chart it said I was Type O Positive: so this test kit worked and I have confirmed the correct result.

Amanda Barco
4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to use, but...
Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2022
Verified Purchase
When I got the test kit I first read the instructions (which is important) and then I went to their website and watched the step-by-step instructional video which was most helpful. I do recommend people wanting to use this kit take their time and follow the instructions before starting. Everything I needed came in the kit. I do recommend putting down some paper towels just in case things get messy. Everything went well but the little sticks that come with it to measure the blood with are really tiny (think miniature pipes) and really aren't very practical. It ended up being a guessing game with how much blood I needed for each dot because it was near impossible to fill those little cups on the sticks up. After I finished struggling with that the rest of it was a breeze. I do recommend you have a bandaid readily available to cover your finger. My finger healed a couple of days later and bleeding doesn't last long once you bandage it up. Besides the sticks with tiny cups part everything else was easy.
